{"id": "552", "instruction": "We now define an algorithm: The definition of a(n) is the least number m for which either 2^m + 1 or 2^m - 1 is divisible by 4n + 1, where n represents the number of pairs of cards in a Mongean shuffle. Given the input x_list (a series of values): [64, 65, 66, 67, 68, 69, 70, 71, 72, 73], determine the corresponding output sequence y_list.\n\nOptions:\nA. [14, 89, 31, 139, 17, 51, 40, 41, 73, 151]\nB. [11, 81, 23, 131, 9, 43, 32, 33, 65, 143]\nC. [6, 86, 28, 136, 14, 48, 37, 38, 70, 148]\nD. [13, 80, 22, 130, 8, 42, 31, 32, 64, 142]\nE. [7, 83, 25, 133, 11, 45, 34, 35, 67, 145]\nF. [5, 82, 24, 132, 10, 44, 33, 34, 66, 144]\nG. [10, 87, 29, 137, 15, 49, 38, 39, 71, 149]\nH. [12, 88, 30, 138, 16, 50, 39, 40, 72, 150]\nI. [9, 85, 27, 135, 13, 47, 36, 37, 69, 147]\nJ. [8, 84, 26, 134, 12, 46, 35, 36, 68, 146]", "output": "J"}
